headline: Globe Life And GL.PR.D: Undervalued Investment Class With Growth Potential
summary: Globe Life's GL.PR.D baby bond offers 6.79% yield, 4.25% coupon, strong ratings, below-par pricing, and solid 10-year NAV returns. See why GL stock is a hold.

headline: 3 Reasons to Avoid GL and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Although Globe Life (currently trading at $128.88 per share) has gained 5.5% over the last six months, it has trailed the S&P 500’s 11.3% return during that period. This was partly due to its softer quarterly results and might have investors contemplating their next move.
